'''Spaarti Creations''' was a unique factory on the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Cartao/Legends|Cartao]]. It was situated among a group of forested hills north of [[Foulahn City]] and three [[Kilometer/Legends|kilometers]] northwest of [[Triv Spaceport]]. It was over a kilometer at its largest and rising three stories. It was commented that it was "an architectural version of a weed patch". It had three satellite facilities called "Outlinks" that stretched into the forested areas north and west of the main facility. Raw materials and finished products were stored there and a third one was used as a worker barracks.

Using a "fluid retooling" unique to their [[Species/Legends|species]], they could adjust the Spaarti factory overnight to produce virtually any product, and the results were almost always superior to similar items on the market. But in the [[Standard year/Legends|year]] [[21 BBY/Legends|21 BBY]], the factory was destroyed by a remote-steered [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Republic]] [[Gunship/Legends|Gunship]] that crashed on the roof and started a fire, that melted the priceless [[Cranscoc]] technology.

Spaarti Creations was notable for creating the [[Spaarti cloning cylinder]]s, notably used by [[Emperor Palpatine (reference book)|Emperor Palpatine]] and [[Mitth'raw'nuruodo/Legends|Grand Admiral Thrawn]] to create clones for their own purposes. 

